  "tune": "Boylston",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Blest be the tie that binds Our hearts in Christian love; The fellowship of kindred minds Is like to that above.",
    "v2": "Before our Father&#39;s throne We pour our ardent prayers; Our fears, our hopes, our aims are one Our comforts and our cares.",
    "v3": "We share each other&#39;s woes, Our mutual burdens bear; And often for each other flows The sympathizing tear.",
    "v4": "When we asunder part, It gives us inward pain; But we shall still be joined in heart, And hope to meet again.",
    "v5": "This glorious hope revives Our courage by the way; While each in expectation lives, And longs to see the day."
  },
